HEADWORD: Gondwanaland
<hw>Gondwanaland</hw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
hypothetical continent that (according to plate tectonic theory) broke
up later into India and Australia and Africa and South America and
Antarctica. See <er>plate tectonics</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

